OL,3,CSigns come down for Clean Air Zone
OL,5,FWork has begun to take down hundreds
OL,6,Fof Clean Air Zone signs as the
OL,7,Fcontroversial scheme is "finally put
OL,8,Fto bed".
OL,10,FThe divisive project across Greater
OL,11,FManchester has cost more the
OL,12,FGovernment more than #100m, after they
OL,13,Finstructed local leaders to bring down
OL,14,Fnitrogen dioxide levels in 2017.
OL,16,FMore than 1,300 signs were installed
OL,17,Facross Greater Manchester, warning
OL,18,Fmotorists of daily charges on certain
OL,19,Fvehicles. But in early 2022, the
OL,20,Fscheme was paused due to public
OL,21,Fbacklash.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/10
