OL,3,CSigns come down for Clean Air Zone
OL,5,FBury council leader Eamonn O'Brien,
OL,6,Fwho is the Clean Air lead for Greater
OL,7,FManchester, said: "We've always been
OL,8,Ffocused on doing what's right for
OL,9,FGreater Manchester, and by
OL,10,Faccelerating investment in our public
OL,11,Ftransport network, we're showing that
OL,12,Fit's possible to improve air quality
OL,13,Ffaster than if a charging Clean Air
OL,14,FZone had been introduced.
OL,16,F"Investment in the Bee Network is
OL,17,Fenabling more people to choose
OL,18,Fcleaner, greener ways to get around `
OL,19,Flike public transport and walking or
OL,20,Fcycling ` instead of driving.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/10
